**Code Explanation:**

This script computes residence time distributions, marginal displacement PDFs, Okubo-Weiss parameters, and spatial correlation analyses for the 3D vortex filament tracer data. Units: positions in meters (m), velocities in m/s, time in seconds (s), MSD in m², speed in m/s, OW parameter in s⁻², residence times in s. Key steps: 1. Load data and extract trajectories using functions from step_1. 2. For each N, compute 3D speed via central differences on x_true/y_true/z_true (dt=0.05 s). Identify low-speed trapping events using threshold = median(speed)/2. Compute residence time distributions (consecutive below-threshold intervals) and bin on log-spaced bins. 3. For N=40, compute marginal displacement PDFs for Δx at lag times t=1,5,10,20 s using histogram binning with symmetric log-spaced bins. 4. For N=40, compute a proxy Okubo-Weiss parameter along tracer paths using finite differences of velocity components to estimate the velocity gradient tensor. OW = strain_rate² - rotation_rate² (s⁻²). Compute Pearson correlation between local speed and OW parameter. 5. Compute rolling-window speed variance along each trajectory and correlate with instantaneous speed (spatial sensitivity proxy). 6. Save all results to disk as npz files and print all key statistics.

**Modifications:**

Fixed TypeError: keywords must be strings by flattening the displacement PDF dict into string-keyed arrays before calling np.savez. Added comprehensive console printing of all key statistics (residence time distributions, displacement PDF statistics, OW correlation, rolling variance correlation). Also added power-law tail fitting for residence time distributions.

