**Code Explanation:**

This script performs power-law fitting of MSD scaling, VACF persistence analysis, and EB parameter computation. It: 1. Reloads raw data from the original files. 2. Computes TAMSD for each tracer individually using vectorized operations, then ensemble-averages. 3. Applies Savitzky-Golay filtering on the log-log derivative to get smooth local slopes. 4. Identifies stable scaling windows by finding plateau regions in the local slope, excluding t < 1s and the last 20% of time range. 5. Fits power laws via linear regression in log-log space within the stable window. 6. Computes VACF for each N and beta class, finds zero-crossing times by linear interpolation. 7. Estimates persistence lengths as v_c * integral of VACF up to zero-crossing, compares to inter-filament spacing. 8. Computes EB(delta_t) = Var(TAMSD_i) / Mean(TAMSD_i)^2 for each lag time and each N. 9. Prints all results in structured format and saves to npz files.

**Modifications:**

Added missing imports, ensured all top-level code is inside if __name__ == '__main__':, fixed indentation, and ensured all file paths use the data/ directory for output.

